# Protected files and secrets

## Never commit, paste, or overwrite

- `server/config/local.env.js` — API keys, DB URI, Twilio, Gmail, tokens
- `server/config/environment/development.js` — local DB config
- `server/firebase.json` — Firebase credentials
- `.env`, `docker.env`
- `*.sqlite` database files
- `server/fileserver/*` — uploaded runtime files

## Edit only with explicit user approval

- `server/app.js` — scheduled jobs, Helmet CSP, server bootstrap
- `server/config/environment/shared.js` — flight schedules, pilot names, equipment limits
- `server/config/environment/production.js` — production settings
- `server/auth/**` — JWT/Passport auth flow
- `server/config/express.js`, `server/config/socketio.js`

## Safe patterns

- Add new env vars to `local.env.sample.js` and document them; do not put real values in tracked files
- When config is needed, tell the user which local file to update instead of writing secrets
- Prefer reading `*.sample.js` templates over live config files
